      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The yeasts, primarily *Saccharomyces cerevisiae* and wild strains, consume sugars in the flour and produce carbon dioxide ($\\text{CO}_2$), which is what creates the rise. Simultaneously, lactic acid bacteria (LAB) consume sugars to produce lactic and acetic acids. These gases and acids work together: the $\\text{CO}_2$ provides lift, while the acids flavor the bread, and they collectively create the acidic environment necessary for both organisms to actively thrive.",
      "source": "target",
